From b5e40067f069c153bf029bc1974becbd28cccf41 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sarika Sharma <sarishar@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Wed, 20 Aug 2025 22:06:43 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] UPSTREAM:PROTOCOL: nl80211: fix memory leak in GET_STATION
 command

In get_sta_handler(), memory is allocated to store link-level statistics.
However, this memory is only freed in one specific call path—via
i802_get_inact_sec(). Other paths, such as nl80211_get_link_signal(), lack
the corresponding memory deallocation logic, resulting in a memory leak
during MLO hwsim test cases.

